				<title>Article Names</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-76680/scp-series#post-4718468</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2020 19:43:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>LeafLock</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4075235</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I don't know if this has been discussed (or if there is a quick/easy way to do it), but would it be acceptable/feasible to have the SCP names listed in their proper articles next to their number? I.e. an article would display SCP-352 &quot;Lilith&quot; at the header. It seems odd to me that many articles don't contain their &quot;names&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
